  "faq": {
    "title": "FAQ",
    "q1": "How are psychologists verified?",
    "a1": "All psychologists go through a thorough verification process including diploma validation, license checks, and professional reference verification.",
    "q2": "How much does a session cost?",
    "a2": "Session prices vary by psychologist and typically range from 50 to 200 GEL. Each psychologist sets their own rates.",
    "q3": "Can I cancel a session?",
    "a3": "Yes, you can cancel up to 24 hours before the session for a full refund. Cancellations within 24 hours may receive a partial refund.",
    "q4": "What languages are supported?",
    "a4": "Our platform supports Georgian, English, and Russian. Many psychologists offer sessions in multiple languages.",
    "q5": "What if I have an emergency?",
    "a5": "If you are experiencing a mental health emergency, please call 112 or visit the nearest emergency room. Our platform is not designed for crisis intervention.",
    "q6": "Does insurance cover sessions?",
    "a6": "Currently, insurance coverage varies. We recommend checking with your insurance provider about mental health coverage.",
    "q7": "Can I meet my therapist in person?",
    "a7": "TalkRest is an online platform. Some psychologists may offer in-person sessions independently, but all sessions on our platform are conducted online."
  },
